    <!-- Architecture -->
    <section class="dark-section">
        <div class="container-narrow">
            <h2>System Architecture</h2>
            <p>How it works (5 core layers)</p>

            <div class="architecture-grid">
                <div class="architecture-layer">
                    <span class="layer-number">1</span>
                    <h4>Ingress & Validation</h4>
                    <p><strong>What it does:</strong> Receives webhooks from any form provider, validates required fields, normalizes data formats.</p>
                    <p><strong>What it prevents:</strong> Malformed data reaching your CRM. Partial submissions causing errors.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="architecture-layer">
                    <span class="layer-number">2</span>
                    <h4>Persistence Layer</h4>
                    <p><strong>What it does:</strong> Writes every lead to a secure datastore (Airtable/Sheets) before routing.</p>
                    <p><strong>What it prevents:</strong> Total data loss if CRM is down. Gives you a source of truth.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="architecture-layer">
                    <span class="layer-number">3</span>
                    <h4>Routing Engine</h4>
                    <p><strong>What it does:</strong> Sends leads to the correct CRM, assigns to the right team, applies business rules.</p>
                    <p><strong>What it prevents:</strong> Leads going to the wrong place. Manual re-routing work.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="architecture-layer">
                    <span class="layer-number">4</span>
                    <h4>Monitoring & Retry</h4>
                    <p><strong>What it does:</strong> Detects timeouts, auth failures, rate limits. Retries failed requests up to 3 times with delays.</p>
                    <p><strong>What it prevents:</strong> Temporary failures becoming permanent losses.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="architecture-layer">
                    <span class="layer-number">5</span>
                    <h4>Audit & Alert</h4>
                    <p><strong>What it does:</strong> Logs every action with timestamps. Sends alerts on failure. Creates queryable history.</p>
                    <p><strong>What it prevents:</strong> "What happened to this lead?" conversations. Compliance gaps. Mystery losses.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p style="margin-top: 48px; font-size: 20px;" class="highlight-text">
                Most businesses connect forms directly to CRMs.<br>
                That works — until it doesn't.<br><br>
                This system adds the reliability layer that production environments require.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

